flowRoot.flowPara: New system status menu designed for quickly checking on system statuses or for quickly toggling settings. That's it.

Submenus are gone due to their poor ability to disclose options. The menu can focus on presenting things more directly without hiding toggles. Settings are also more straightforwardly accessed by going to the Settings app than through links in the status menu.

Non-toggleable system-level status items, like battery level, print job(s), software updates, active services, etc. are simply shown as a line with the icon and text when active. Clicking on them opens the relevant software.
Icons for these items also appear in the topbar when relevant. (e.g. battery is always active so it's always there, printing is more transient.)
These are not application statuses, those are what notifications are for.
Clicking on the bubbles toggles on or off the setting within it and that's it.
Blue is active, grey is inactive. A label describes the toggle, and icons reflect the status.
There is potential for many kinds of toggles that could be exposed.

For cases like where the toggle affects a setting with options, e.g. Wi-Fi, the label will indicate the presence of those options with an icon. Clicking the label will spawn an appropriate popup to change the option, e.g. the network selector in the case of Wi-Fi.
